               <history>
                   <origin>
                       <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800">
                       </origDate>
                   </origin>
                   <provenance>The commissioners mentioned in the manuscript up to fol. 104r
                   are <persName ref="PRS12660BatraMaryam">Batra Māryām</persName> with
                   "his beloved"<persName role="patron" ref="PRS12661WaldaHanna">
                 Walda Ḥannā</persName>, with the scribe <persName ref="PRS12656MasoraDengel">Maṣora
                 Dǝngǝl</persName>.
                 On fol. 104v "the children of <persName role="patron"
                 ref="PRS12662Zaparaqlitos">Zaṗārāqliṭos</persName>" are mentioned.
                 and on fol. 109r  <persName role="patron"
                 ref="PRS12663GabraMaryam">Gabra Māryām</persName>, Maṣora
                 Dǝngǝl and, over an erasure, <persName role="patron"
                 ref="PRS12664AmdaGiyorgis">ʿĀmda Giyorgis</persName> are mentioned.
                 The manuscript was later bought by the Russian diplomat
                     <persName ref="PRS7674Orlov">Alexander Orlov</persName>
                       and acquired by the Asian Museum on <date>10 September 1903</date>
                 </provenance>
               </history>


